**Ethernet Frame**
- Preamble
	- 7 bytes
	- 56 alternating 1s & 0s for sync
- SFD
	- 1 byte
	- Start Frame Delimiter
	- preamble is over
- Destination MAC Addr
	- 6 byte
- Source MAC addr
	- 6 byte
- EtherType
	- 2 byte
	- Describes data contained
- Payload
	- 46 - 1500 bytes
	- Layer 3
- FCS
	- Frame check sequence
	- Redundancy check

MAC Address

- Ethernet Media Access Control Address
- Physical address of network addapter
- 48bits / 6 bytes long
-   ![8c:2d:aa: 
    Organizationally Unique 
    Identifier (OUI) 
    (the manufacturer) 
    Network Interface

**Duplex**
- Half-duplex
	- Sending or receiving. Only one at a time
	- All LAN hubs are
	- Not as common nowadays
- CSMA / CD
	- CS - Carrier Sense
		- Is there a carrier?
		- Is there signal avail?
	- MA - Multiple Acces
		- More than one device on network
	- CD - Collision Detect
		- Detect if data collides
	- Listen for opening, don’t' transmit if busy
- Full-duplex
	- Data sent & received at same time
	- Most common for switches
	- Does not have to go through hoops like above
